And one day he will come back and take us to be with him.

18:37.334 --> 18:37.554
All right.

18:37.774 --> 18:44.582
So he's saying this to them as often they are the disciples are totally confused and not actually understanding what he's saying.

18:44.983 --> 18:51.090
And so they're visibly upset about this idea that Jesus is saying that he's going to leave them.

18:51.202 --> 18:57.250
And so Jesus responds back to them and he says this in John 14, he says, hey, don't let your hearts be troubled.

18:58.051 --> 19:00.334
You believe in God, believe also in me.

19:00.894 --> 19:06.702
My father's house has many rooms, if that were not so, would I have not told you that I'm going there to prepare a place for you?

19:06.742 --> 19:12.910
And if I go and I prepare a place for you, I will come back and I'll take you to be with me, that you also may be where I am.

19:13.391 --> 19:16.995
You know the way to the place where I am going.

19:17.936 --> 19:19.218
Thomas said to him, Lord,

19:19.490 --> 19:22.434
We don't know where you're going, so how can we know the way?

19:23.235 --> 19:27.339
Jesus answered, I am the way and the truth and the life.

19:27.359 --> 19:30.083
No one comes to the Father except through me.

19:30.744 --> 19:34.368
Now that statement causes a lot of people to get tripped up.

19:34.468 --> 19:37.191
It's caused me to get tripped up in certain seasons of my life.

19:37.211 --> 19:39.975
And so I'm gonna come back in a few minutes and talk a little bit more about that.

19:40.635 --> 19:43.619
He says, if you really know me, you will know my Father as well.

19:44.200 --> 19:47.364
From now on, you do know Him and you have seen Him.

19:48.144 --> 19:49.426
Philip said, Lord,

19:49.762 --> 19:52.226
Show us the Father, and that will be enough for us."

19:52.726 --> 19:54.950
Jesus answered, don't you know me, Philip?

19:55.270 --> 20:00.578
Even after I have been among you such a long time, anyone who has seen me has seen the Father.

20:00.999 --> 20:03.322
How can you say, show us the Father?

20:03.562 --> 20:06.126
Don't you believe that I am the Father and that the Father is in me?

20:06.206 --> 20:08.970
The words I say to you, I do not speak on my own authority.

20:09.351 --> 20:14.098
Rather, it is the Father living in me who is doing His work.

20:14.658 --> 20:21.967
Believe me when I say that I'm the father and the fathers in me, or at least believe on the evidence of the works themselves.

20:23.509 --> 20:25.171
And that really resonated with John.

20:25.191 --> 20:35.684
And I think that's why John organizes gospel in the way that he did around certain signs and wonders that were pointing to the evidence of who Jesus actually was.

20:36.865 --> 20:40.850
It's interesting, this whole concept, because they're deeply confused.

20:41.122 --> 20:43.805
And I don't think that they're trying to cause trouble here.

20:43.846 --> 20:45.187
They're just trying to figure it out.

20:45.788 --> 20:50.494
And Jesus is saying, hey, if you know me, you know the Father as well.

20:51.195 --> 20:53.818
To the degree that you know me, you know God.

20:53.858 --> 21:05.874
Now, when you understand that, if you believe what Jesus is actually saying there, to the degree that you know me, you know God, that should revolutionize what you think about God the Father.

21:06.914 --> 21:08.657
So let me ask you a question, all right?

21:08.677 --> 21:18.171
You don't have to answer this out loud, but when you hear the word of the name God, and then you hear the word or the name Jesus, is there a tension for you?

21:19.953 --> 21:23.959
Like in other words, it's one of those names you like better.

21:25.622 --> 21:28.626
Is it one of those names that you feel more comfortable with?

21:29.826 --> 21:36.576
Like for some of you, maybe it's you feel more comfortable with Jesus because the whole idea of God up there, you have no idea.

21:36.596 --> 21:37.978
You can't see him.

21:39.140 --> 21:40.302
And so it's brought some confusion.

21:40.322 --> 21:42.605
Or maybe for some of you, you're totally cool with the God thing.

21:42.966 --> 21:45.710
Like the whole concept of God, you talk about God, you pray to God.

21:45.990 --> 21:49.395
But then once you start talking about Jesus, that kind of creates all this weirdness for you.

21:49.455 --> 21:50.297
Right?

21:50.617 --> 21:54.002
And what I would say is that there's any tension inside of you,

21:54.562 --> 22:02.696
When you think about the word of name God and the word of name Jesus, if there's any tension that is involved there for you, you got a little bit of work to do.

22:03.397 --> 22:07.004
Because what Jesus is saying is, I came to remove that tension.

22:07.665 --> 22:14.877
There should be no tension between this idea, this concept of God and this idea, this concept of me.

22:15.118 --> 22:19.826
I have come here to remove the mystery of what God is like.

22:20.610 --> 22:26.258
I have come to show you, so you don't have to wonder anymore what God is, who God is.

22:26.719 --> 22:32.326
And so when Philip is asking these questions to Jesus again, I don't think he's trying to be offensive.

22:32.887 --> 22:36.632
I don't think he's in any way being disrespectful to Jesus.

22:37.133 --> 22:42.561
He's just saying, hey, like we get Jesus that you're not a mere mortal.

22:43.121 --> 22:49.330
Like we've seen these signs, we've seen these wonders, we've heard your teachings, we know you're not normal.

22:49.730 --> 22:51.072
You're not mortal.

22:51.092 --> 22:51.773
We get that.

22:52.354 --> 22:55.078
But you being God?

22:55.899 --> 22:59.544
Like in a body sitting here in the room with us?

23:00.245 --> 23:01.928
Those like, just show us the Father.

23:02.569 --> 23:03.730
Just show us God.

23:03.791 --> 23:04.732
Like we're confused.

23:04.752 --> 23:05.633
That will be enough.

23:05.673 --> 23:09.960
He's like, we have the temple and we have scriptures and all that is very helpful.

23:10.260 --> 23:11.842
But show us the Father.

23:11.902 --> 23:12.744
Just make it clear.

23:12.804 --> 23:17.170
And Jesus is like, you want to see the Father?

23:18.658 --> 23:21.981
What do you think that I've been doing the past three years?

23:22.922 --> 23:26.126
Why do you think I drag you jokers around with me everywhere that I go?

23:26.146 --> 23:30.490
I didn't come here just to provide you guys with a bunch of new Bible stories.

23:31.091 --> 23:35.535
The reason that I came is so that you could know what the Father was like.

23:36.316 --> 23:39.479
And so the Gospels are not just stories about Jesus.

23:39.860 --> 23:45.906
The Gospel documents Jesus' example and explanation of what God is like.

23:46.882 --> 23:56.837
And that is so important because since the beginning of time, since the human species has existed, we've been trying to figure this mystery out, right?

23:57.097 --> 24:06.792
And so you look back at all the different tribes, all the different civilizations, all the different nations, everybody from the beginning of time has been trying to figure out this mystery called God.

24:06.812 --> 24:13.362
There's been something inside of us that knows, like that somehow something has to be holding this whole thing together.

24:13.698 --> 24:17.683
Right inside of every human being, there's this void that says there's gotta be more to this.

24:17.783 --> 24:20.567
Like, I wanna figure this out and we're drawn to that.

24:21.228 --> 24:34.444
Anthropologists tell us that there have been, since the beginning of time, over 18,000 different gods, different goddesses, different animals, different objects that have been worshiped by mankind.

24:35.445 --> 24:37.428
I don't know if that number is exactly right.

24:37.508 --> 24:40.532
I don't know how they came to that number, but it wouldn't surprise me at all.

24:41.073 --> 24:42.194
It makes sense.

24:42.818 --> 24:45.983
We were created trying to figure out this mystery.

24:46.104 --> 24:48.308
What is God like?

24:49.109 --> 24:51.513
And until Jesus came, nobody really knew.

24:51.553 --> 24:53.196
Nobody really knew.

24:53.256 --> 24:58.004
God made it clear as he possibly could through Jesus to us mortal people.

24:58.385 --> 25:01.771
He sends his son in the flesh to dwell among us.

25:01.811 --> 25:06.138
He came to show us what God is like and who God loves.

25:07.561 --> 25:08.242
And so when we

25:08.354 --> 25:16.327
When we talk about these gospels, when we talk about these stories, you have to understand Jesus didn't just have an explanation of God.

25:16.708 --> 25:20.394
Jesus is the best explanation of God.

25:21.556 --> 25:23.198
You see the distinction between those two?

25:24.040 --> 25:35.218
Some of you kind of read through the Bible when you're thinking, oh, Jesus is kind of giving us an explanation of what God's like, but the reality is he is the best explanation for us of what God is like.

25:35.618 --> 25:39.123
have to base our conclusion from our personal experience.

25:39.143 --> 25:42.328
We don't have to base our conclusion on what God is like from nature.

25:42.789 --> 25:45.654
If you want to know what God is like, He's like Jesus.

25:46.976 --> 25:47.897
He's just like Jesus.

25:48.778 --> 25:57.231
Now, I want to go back to this claim that Jesus made, that I told you, trip some people up and I'll be honest, it's trip me up in times.

25:57.933 --> 26:04.082
This single statement that Jesus made, if I'm honest, there have been times in my life that I kind of wished

26:04.610 --> 26:06.892
In that moment, I kind of wish Jesus hadn't said this.

26:07.353 --> 26:09.695
I kind of wished I could ignore this statement.

26:09.715 --> 26:15.200
I kind of wish I could have found a way to position what Jesus was saying in a different way.

26:15.261 --> 26:18.844
And maybe it's because there's someone that I loved deeply that was far from God.

26:19.345 --> 26:20.986
And this was very troubling to me.

26:21.347 --> 26:24.069
But this statement right here is where a lot of you guys get hung up.

26:24.370 --> 26:29.094
And it's where Jesus said, I am the way and I am the truth and I am the life.

26:29.134 --> 26:32.978
No one comes to the Father except through me.

26:33.890 --> 26:43.621
Now what bothers a lot of us about a statement like that is we think could there really be just one answer to this human dilemma.

26:44.342 --> 26:58.298
I mean like can't there be multiple ways, can't Buddhist kind of have their own way and their own path and then Muslims can kind of have their own way and their own path and then Christians can kind of have their own way and their own path.

26:58.659 --> 27:01.522
Some of you would even say something like, I mean,

27:01.890 --> 27:04.033
Aren't all religions basically the same?

27:04.113 --> 27:09.782
They just use kind of different rituals and maybe different names to kind of explain what's going on in the universe.

27:10.483 --> 27:12.286
And that's exactly where some of you are.

27:12.806 --> 27:13.888
The problem with that is this.

27:14.369 --> 27:16.572
It's really offensive to say all religions are the same.

27:16.933 --> 27:18.815
Muslims don't think they're the same as Christians.

27:18.856 --> 27:20.538
Christians don't think they're the same as Muslims.

27:20.598 --> 27:21.680
Buddhists don't think they're the same.

27:21.740 --> 27:28.330
That's offensive to everybody because nobody actually thinks when they're in that, they're just like the other.

27:28.350 --> 27:31.154
They are different except

27:31.554 --> 27:39.325
In this, every religion gives you a path to achieve your ultimate ending.

27:40.507 --> 27:40.707
Right?

27:40.767 --> 27:45.474
So if your ultimate goal is enlightenment, Buddhism has a path for you.

27:46.375 --> 27:52.003
If your ultimate goal is favored with Allah, Muslims have a path for that.

27:52.845 --> 27:56.690
If you're trying to find favor with God, Catholicism has a path for that.

27:57.122 --> 27:57.302
Right?

27:57.543 --> 28:02.930
And the common thread between all religions is that they were created by humans.

28:04.312 --> 28:05.514
That's what atheists get right.

28:05.954 --> 28:11.982
That's probably the only thing I can agree with most of the time with most atheists when I'm in a conversation with them is you're right.

28:12.523 --> 28:19.032
Religions were created by people who are trying to figure out what do you have to do to get close to God?

28:19.373 --> 28:21.556
What do you have to do to be accepted by God?

28:21.656 --> 28:24.319
What do you have to do to find favor with God?

28:24.580 --> 28:26.162
In that, right?

28:26.434 --> 28:27.275
They are correct.

28:27.335 --> 28:29.459
These religions were created by people.

28:29.719 --> 28:34.106
Every religion teaches you some kind of path to get to God.

28:35.207 --> 28:36.950
Here's what you have to do to get God's intention.

28:37.210 --> 28:38.512
Here's what you have to do to get God's love.

28:38.692 --> 28:40.535
Here's what you have to do to get God's grace.

28:40.555 --> 28:46.965
You have to go through this process, take on this religion, take on this pathway, and then you can find favor with God.

28:47.486 --> 28:55.698
So we have this construct about God as this elusive being that we have to earn our way to Him.

28:56.866 --> 29:03.735
But I'm telling you, any God who forces you to earn his love is not worthy of your worship.

29:05.297 --> 29:11.546
Say that again, any God who forces you to earn his love is not worthy of your worship.

29:12.267 --> 29:18.295
That's why I believe Jesus does not fall or count as actually a religion.

29:18.856 --> 29:22.120
See, Jesus didn't come to tell us what we need to do to get to God.

29:22.701 --> 29:26.226
Jesus came to show us what God would do to get to us.

29:27.042 --> 29:32.127
That's completely different than any other world religion.

29:32.667 --> 29:34.929
This is not like religion 2.0.

29:34.950 --> 29:37.412
It's going to be a little bit easier this time around.

29:37.432 --> 29:39.234
No, it's totally different.

29:39.254 --> 29:42.196
This isn't about building some construct to get to God.

29:42.417 --> 29:47.662
It's not about climbing some kind of ladder to religious rituals or goods or deeds.

29:47.942 --> 29:48.643
It's none of that.

29:49.303 --> 29:51.025
This is God saying, no, no, no, no, listen.

29:51.185 --> 29:52.947
You don't got to build this pathway to me.

29:52.987 --> 29:56.530
I'm going to come to you to once and for all show you.

29:57.122 --> 29:59.225
what I'm like and who I love.

29:59.706 --> 30:07.338
And I just believe that this is so important that you understand this difference, this uniqueness of what Jesus has done for us, right?

30:07.358 --> 30:10.743
He says, I am the way, the truth, and the life.

30:11.905 --> 30:22.642
And I think sometimes it's confusing to me because I actually have friends who are totally cool with the God thing, but they're not cool with the Jesus thing.

30:23.202 --> 30:27.166
And so once we start going down that pathway, they're like, yeah, I'm tapping out.

30:27.226 --> 30:28.788
Like I can't go there.

30:28.808 --> 30:33.433
I do believe there is mysteriously some God, but like the whole Jesus thing.

30:33.633 --> 30:40.821
But what's so interesting to me about that is God is the name that we actually use when we talk about us searching for Him.

30:41.342 --> 30:47.669
Jesus is the name that we use when we talk about God searching for us, coming after us.

30:49.711 --> 30:52.274
My wife and I have a daughter, her name's Pepper.

30:52.930 --> 30:54.392
She's two and a half years old.

30:54.432 --> 30:57.315
That's a picture ever from earlier this week.

30:57.976 --> 31:01.641
We were on a daddy daughter date and my wife was out some girlfriends.

31:01.941 --> 31:06.186
And so I took her to the park and it's a little park in our neighborhood.

31:06.286 --> 31:10.732
And like most, you know, people there were letting her kids slide down slides and stuff.

31:10.772 --> 31:15.698
And my wife often accuses me of putting kids in positions that they really shouldn't be in at their

31:15.810 --> 31:16.471
You know, age.

31:17.252 --> 31:18.173
And I get, she's right.

31:18.253 --> 31:18.693
I get that.

31:18.753 --> 31:20.035
But I can't help myself.

31:20.135 --> 31:20.976
And I saw a tree.

31:21.276 --> 31:23.859
And I was like, I love climbing trees as a kid.

31:23.899 --> 31:25.161
That was like the coolest thing ever.

31:25.541 --> 31:26.522
So I'm like, she's two and a half.

31:26.542 --> 31:27.643
She can kind of walk now.

31:27.724 --> 31:28.845
So let's try it.

31:29.606 --> 31:32.769
And so I set her up on the bottom limb of this tree.

31:32.849 --> 31:35.412
Hard to tell from the picture, but it was up over my head.

31:35.432 --> 31:38.716
So let's say seven foot, like I place her up there in that tree.

31:38.996 --> 31:39.497
Not two.

31:39.517 --> 31:43.341
I mean, like, she's not going to die if she falls out of this tree, right?

31:43.482 --> 31:43.922
I mean,

31:44.482 --> 31:48.486
She's gonna get scraped up, maybe break an ankle, something, but she's okay.

31:48.506 --> 31:49.207
And I'm right there.

31:49.287 --> 31:52.271
In my defense, I'm right there, except for in this moment, because I'm taking a picture.

31:52.351 --> 31:54.873
So other than that, I'm right there.

31:55.334 --> 31:57.696
So she's having a great time up there for a while.

31:58.037 --> 32:02.642
And then I'm like, Pepper, it's probably time to get down, let Daddy get you down.

32:03.102 --> 32:05.705
And then she just starts screaming bloody murder, right?

32:06.046 --> 32:10.130
And there are other mostly moms here at the playground with their kids.

32:10.306 --> 32:17.842
all staring at me like not only is he a bad dad that puts his kid up in a tree but apparently he abuses her as well because

32:17.954 --> 32:20.597
This kid does not want him to touch her, right?

32:20.938 --> 32:21.959
And so she starts screaming.

32:21.979 --> 32:22.680
She doesn't want to get down.

32:22.760 --> 32:28.727
And then she decides that she wants her mom to get her down out of the tree, which is fine, but mom is not there, right?

32:28.808 --> 32:31.311
And then she wants her grandma that she calls cookie.

32:31.611 --> 32:33.433
She's screaming for cookie for a solid minute.

32:33.694 --> 32:36.898
I'm like, cookie is about 400 miles from here.

32:37.238 --> 32:38.239
She's not here to get you.

32:38.480 --> 32:41.564
She starts calling out to her brothers to come get her out of the tree.

32:41.984 --> 32:46.770
And I'm trying to have a rational conversation with her that goes something like this, pepper,

32:47.778 --> 32:51.001
You don't have another option, right?

32:51.242 --> 32:53.284
That has to get you down out of the tree.

32:54.085 --> 32:56.707
Nobody else is coming for you, right?

32:56.727 --> 32:57.268
This is it.

32:57.809 --> 32:59.931
I'm the only option that you have.

33:00.451 --> 33:06.097
Now, what's interesting to me, when Jesus says, I am the way, the truth, and the life.

33:06.157 --> 33:08.520
No one comes to the Father except through me.

33:08.880 --> 33:14.386
Why does Jesus cut out all the other options, right?

33:15.554 --> 33:20.299
I don't think in this instance, he's saying he's superior, although he clearly is.

33:20.939 --> 33:26.745
I think what he's communicating when he says, I'm the way, the truth, and the life, no one comes to the Father except through me.

33:27.826 --> 33:33.732
And his love and his kindness, what he's saying to all of us is, hey, nobody else is coming.

33:35.493 --> 33:35.634
Right?

33:35.654 --> 33:36.895
Nobody else is coming for you.

33:37.816 --> 33:42.080
God has sent me to this earth, his son, his representative.

33:42.540 --> 33:44.242
Nobody else is coming.

33:45.026 --> 34:04.365
So why in the world would you spend your entire life trying to get approval of a God who's not coming after you, but instead has created some kind of elaborate ladder of works, indeed, and religion that you have to climb, hoping that one day you could achieve his love and his grace and his mercy?

34:04.746 --> 34:13.074
See, if God is love and everything that God does is a manifestation of love, it just makes sense to me that he'd pursue us.

34:13.666 --> 34:15.068
that he would come after us.

34:15.729 --> 34:18.934
And he says, I am the way, the truth, and the life.

34:19.615 --> 34:20.235
The life.

34:20.436 --> 34:22.919
In other words, I am a perfect fit for your soul.

34:22.959 --> 34:25.223
I created you this way.

34:26.104 --> 34:27.967
I created you this way.

34:28.087 --> 34:29.729
I'm the perfect fit for you.

34:29.769 --> 34:32.834
He came to change our existence.

34:32.854 --> 34:34.977
He didn't come just to change your thoughts or your beliefs.

34:35.277 --> 34:36.579
He came to change your existence.

34:36.839 --> 34:41.426
Because isn't it true that some of you don't really have life, what you have is an existence.

34:41.986 --> 34:43.649
You have this void inside of you.

34:43.909 --> 34:48.275
And you've tried, just like me, to fill that void with all kinds of things, right?

34:48.716 --> 34:50.238
You've tried intellectual thinking.

34:50.799 --> 34:51.641
You've tried money.

34:51.681 --> 34:52.963
You've tried power.

34:53.223 --> 34:54.485
You've tried popularity.

34:54.725 --> 35:02.076
You've tried more and more of all those things, hoping that somehow it would fill this void inside of you and make you feel complete and give you purpose.

35:02.697 --> 35:03.619
But it hasn't.

35:04.941 --> 35:06.543
And what Jesus is saying, I have come.

35:06.703 --> 35:07.204
I am the way.

35:07.344 --> 35:07.825
I am the truth.

35:07.985 --> 35:08.806
I am the life.

35:09.227 --> 35:11.250
I am the perfect fit for you.

35:11.778 --> 35:26.898
and you will feel most alive when you're most fully loved, and you will be most fully loved by Jesus Christ himself.

35:27.010 --> 35:35.122
You and I were sitting down right now just having a cup of coffee and we're talking about faith and we're talking about all this and maybe you would share with me.

35:35.262 --> 35:36.063
I just don't know.

35:36.083 --> 35:36.944
I don't know Pete.

35:37.025 --> 35:38.987
I don't know if I can cross that line.

35:39.148 --> 35:40.089
I get it.

35:40.490 --> 35:43.995
There is definitely a mystery out there and there is a God and it's not me.

35:45.437 --> 35:49.042
But I don't know if I can believe in Jesus.

35:49.890 --> 36:06.246
I think what I would probably say to you, I'd probably say a lot of different things, but one thing I would wanna do is just kinda lean across the table and say to you, I understand that you might not believe in Jesus, but isn't it true that your soul deeply misses him?

36:07.667 --> 36:12.211
Isn't it true that there's still some kind of void there for you and your life?

36:13.092 --> 36:19.218
And I honestly believe the most important question that you can ever ask yourself is who do I believe that Jesus

36:19.426 --> 36:25.813
is, because our relationship with Jesus, it's the most important issue of our lives.

36:27.255 --> 36:28.697
Last verse, I'll wrap up with this.

36:29.257 --> 36:37.607
This is 1 John chapter 5, it says, and this is the testimony, God has given us eternal life, and this life is in His Son.

36:37.667 --> 36:43.794
Whoever has this Son has life, whoever does not have the Son of God, does not have life.

36:44.226 --> 36:51.657
I write these things to you who believe in the name of the Son of God so that you may know that you have eternal life.

36:52.819 --> 36:53.340
That's simple.

36:53.440 --> 36:54.562
That's what Scripture teaches.

36:54.922 --> 37:00.231
Those who have the Son have life, those who don't have the Son don't have life.

37:00.311 --> 37:04.457
Jesus said, I'm the way, I'm the truth, I'm the life.

37:05.739 --> 37:07.502
No one else is coming for you.

37:08.684 --> 37:09.084
I'm here.

37:09.725 --> 37:10.226
I'm it.

37:10.626 --> 37:12.348
I'm the sole substitution.

37:12.388 --> 37:15.871
I'm going to the cross to do for you what you could not do for yourself.

37:15.931 --> 37:18.874
You could not die a sinless death.

37:20.375 --> 37:24.119
And you can study and you can research every world religion out there.

37:24.159 --> 37:27.643
There is no similar claim to that.

37:28.083 --> 37:31.386
Everything else is about building a construct to get to God.

37:31.406 --> 37:35.530
This is the only example we have of God saying, no, no, no.

37:35.810 --> 37:36.691
You don't have to come to me.

37:37.492 --> 37:39.474
I'm coming to you.

37:40.386 --> 37:43.529
And I'm gonna give some of you today the opportunity to cross that line of faith.

37:43.569 --> 37:45.851
So if you guys would just bow your head and close your eyes.

37:46.872 --> 37:53.218
And if you're watching online, we'd love to invite you to be a part of this part of our service with us.

37:54.340 --> 38:01.026
And for some of you, again, you've never trusted in Jesus as your personal Lord and Savior.

38:01.987 --> 38:03.328
And I want you to do me a favor right now.

38:03.348 --> 38:06.732
I want everybody to do this, just kind of picture like literally like a line of faith.

38:07.933 --> 38:09.234
And you're on one side, right?

38:10.498 --> 38:12.801
And maybe today is the day.

38:12.821 --> 38:19.828
You haven't crossed that line yet, but maybe today is the day you're finally gonna step across that line and just be like, I don't know, for some reason I get it.

38:20.869 --> 38:21.190
I get it.

38:22.271 --> 38:24.734
I get that there should be no tension between God and Jesus.

38:24.814 --> 38:29.639
I get that He came from me, and I wanna give Him my life.

38:31.201 --> 38:34.484
And I wanna give you guys the opportunity to do that today, right?

38:34.564 --> 38:38.709
It's a very simple prayer, just the conversation that you're gonna have in your heart with God.

38:38.749 --> 38:39.890
I'm gonna lead you through it.

38:40.194 --> 38:43.819
And essentially all you're saying is God, I give you my life.

38:44.560 --> 38:46.123
I want to trust in Jesus Christ.

38:47.204 --> 38:49.968
It's that simple.

38:50.009 --> 38:51.591
Just step across that line of faith.

38:51.991 --> 38:58.922
I'm gonna lead you in that prayer in just a second, but before we do that, I would love to know who I'm praying with, right?

38:58.962 --> 39:04.530
And so if you're here and you want to cross that line of faith and you want to pray that prayer, that you want to declare

39:05.218 --> 39:08.381
Ask what Jesus did on the cross to be applied to your sin problem.

39:08.401 --> 39:12.526
If you want to do that today and cross that line, would you do me a favor right now and just raise your hand high?

39:13.347 --> 39:14.588
Just want to know who I'm going to be praying with.

39:14.628 --> 39:15.549
Go ahead, raise your hand high.

39:15.990 --> 39:16.410
Hold it up high.

39:16.430 --> 39:17.812
It's the biggest decision of your life.

39:19.394 --> 39:21.015
Yeah, dozens and dozens of hands.

39:21.075 --> 39:21.576
Praise God.

39:22.637 --> 39:23.939
All right, you guys can put your hands down.

39:26.621 --> 39:34.450
And just sitting where you're sitting right now, again, whether you're online or you're right here in the room with us, just open up your heart and say, Dear God,

39:35.938 --> 39:38.683
with as much as I understand about you right now.

39:42.689 --> 39:47.658
I want to ask what your son Jesus did on the cross to be applied to my life.

39:51.304 --> 39:52.666
I want to receive that forgiveness.

39:52.747 --> 39:55.491
I understand this is not about my good works.

39:57.174 --> 40:00.139
I understand this is not about my righteousness.

40:00.199 --> 40:01.842
It's about Christ righteousness.

40:04.002 --> 40:06.105
And I wanna ask what he did on the cross to be applied to me.

40:07.606 --> 40:09.489
I wanna give you my life.

40:10.990 --> 40:13.593
I'm gonna trust in you and in you alone.

40:17.618 --> 40:18.559
It's just that simple prayer.

40:19.420 --> 40:27.110
And the Bible tells us, if you confess with your mouth that Jesus is Lord and you believe in your heart that God raised him from the dead, you will be saved.

40:27.410 --> 40:30.834
You and God are gonna have a lot of conversations moving forward.

40:31.394 --> 40:35.698
But right now it's just that simple conversation of I give you my life.

40:37.220 --> 40:44.047
God, there's a lot of us here that have already crossed that line of faith, but today we just needed a reminder of how good you are.

40:45.608 --> 40:50.873
That you didn't leave us to our own devices to figure out this mystery on our own, but you sent your son Jesus Christ.

40:51.134 --> 40:55.178
So there would be no doubt who you are and who you love.

40:55.778 --> 40:59.442
There'd be no doubt about your mercy and your grace and your forgiveness.

40:59.842 --> 41:05.510
There'd be no doubt about the fact that you've embedded inside of every one of us a purpose and a meaning.

41:06.291 --> 41:08.734
And God, we are so grateful for that and we are grateful to you.

41:10.296 --> 41:15.543
So we thank you for meeting us in this place today for it's in your holy and your precious name that we pray.

41:16.685 --> 41:18.227
Amen.

41:18.247 --> 41:23.354
I'm gonna ask you guys to do me a favor because there are dozens of you who raised your hand and say you wanted to cross that line of faith.

41:23.374 --> 41:25.797
I'm gonna ask you to do me one more favor, all right?

41:26.358 --> 41:27.139
And that is this.

41:27.619 --> 41:29.682
Would you just text so easy?

41:29.858 --> 41:30.719
Don't got to stand up.

41:30.739 --> 41:32.060
We're not going to embarrass you in any way.

41:32.360 --> 41:34.282
Could you just text the word Northridge?

41:34.503 --> 41:34.843
One word.

41:35.243 --> 41:38.426
Text the word Northridge to 31616.

41:39.027 --> 41:41.910
We're not going to show up at your house or call you.

41:41.930 --> 41:44.012
We're not even going to call you on the phone, right?

41:44.372 --> 41:49.017
We just want to send you a gift that can encourage you and kind of get you started in the right way.

41:49.417 --> 41:55.003
And can we just take a second out right now to celebrate all those people who cross that line of faith today?

41:55.023 --> 41:55.984
We're so proud of you.

41:57.025 --> 41:58.226
You're so proud of you.

42:01.026 --> 42:03.311
Your life will never be the same again.

42:03.351 --> 42:06.597
I'm not saying it's gonna be an easy walk, an easy path, right?

42:06.918 --> 42:09.403
But your life will never be the same again.

42:09.423 --> 42:14.292
And we're gonna take just a minute, whether you just met Jesus for the first time or you've known Him for a long time.

42:14.312 --> 42:21.106
We're gonna take just a minute to sing a song together and be reminded of the goodness and the kindness of our God.

